<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<PcGts xmlns="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15 http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15/pagecontent.xsd"><Metadata><Creator>xl-export</Creator><Created>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</Created><LastChange>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</LastChange></Metadata><Page imageFilename="" imageWidth="1000" imageHeight="1000"><TextRegion id="r1" custom="type:paragraph"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,1000 0,1000" /><TextLine id="l1" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,40 0,40" /><Baseline points="0,38 1000,38" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I said [—]. He said [—]. I said that I was [—] proud [—].</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l2" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,40 1000,40 1000,80 0,80" /><Baseline points="0,78 1000,78" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He asked me then for my blessing.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l3" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,80 1000,80 1000,120 0,120" /><Baseline points="0,118 1000,118" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>This part is not damaged. I want you to notice that. The</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l4" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,120 1000,120 1000,160 0,160" /><Baseline points="0,158 1000,158" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>folio is clean here, the ink unsmeared, the hand steady.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l5" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,160 1000,160 1000,200 0,200" /><Baseline points="0,198 1000,198" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Some things a man writes carefully because he intends them</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l6" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,200 1000,200 1000,240 0,240" /><Baseline points="0,238 1000,238" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>to last.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l7" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,240 1000,240 1000,280 0,280" /><Baseline points="0,278 1000,278" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He knelt in the garden, in the cold, on the stone path, and</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l8" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,280 1000,280 1000,320 0,320" /><Baseline points="0,318 1000,318" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>he asked me to bless his going. He was not being cruel. He</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l9" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,320 1000,320 1000,360 0,360" /><Baseline points="0,358 1000,358" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>was being — I have thought about the word for two years — he</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l10" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,360 1000,360 1000,400 0,400" /><Baseline points="0,398 1000,398" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>was being exact. He knew what our years together had been</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l11" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,400 1000,400 1000,440 0,440" /><Baseline points="0,438 1000,438" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>and he honored them in the only currency he had left to</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l12" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,440 1000,440 1000,480 0,480" /><Baseline points="0,478 1000,478" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>offer. He was asking me to make it holy because he knew I</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l13" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,480 1000,480 1000,520 0,520" /><Baseline points="0,518 1000,518" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>was the only one who could, for him, and because he could</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l14" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,520 1000,520 1000,560 0,560" /><Baseline points="0,558 1000,558" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>not leave it unholy and remain himself.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l15" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,560 1000,560 1000,600 0,600" /><Baseline points="0,598 1000,598" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I put my hands on his head.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l16" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,600 1000,600 1000,640 0,640" /><Baseline points="0,638 1000,638" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I said the words.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l17" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,640 1000,640 1000,680 0,680" /><Baseline points="0,678 1000,678" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He stood up. He embraced me once, quickly, the way young men</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l18" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,680 1000,680 1000,720 0,720" /><Baseline points="0,718 1000,718" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>embrace when they are afraid of what they feel. He left the</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l19" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,720 1000,720 1000,760 0,760" /><Baseline points="0,758 1000,758" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>garden.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l20" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,760 1000,760 1000,800 0,800" /><Baseline points="0,798 1000,798" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I remained on the path for a long time. I was thinking about</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l21" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,800 1000,800 1000,840 0,840" /><Baseline points="0,838 1000,838" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>a question I had never asked him and now never would:</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l22" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,840 1000,840 1000,880 0,880" /><Baseline points="0,878 1000,878" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>whether, in all those years of learning the craft from me,</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l23" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,880 1000,880 1000,920 0,920" /><Baseline points="0,918 1000,918" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>he had ever felt what I felt — the going-quiet, the</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l24" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,920 1000,920 1000,960 0,960" /><Baseline points="0,958 1000,958" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>particular silence that comes when the hand and the word and</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l25" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,960 1000,960 1000,1000 0,1000" /><Baseline points="0,998 1000,998" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>the meaning arrive together in the same moment, when you are</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine></TextRegion></Page></PcGts>